If you want to **sign up** for a GitHub account, follow these steps:  

---

### **1. Open GitHub Website**  
Go to [GitHub](https://github.com/) in your browser.  

---

### **2. Click on "Sign Up"**  
- On the **top-right corner**, click **"Sign up"** or go directly to [GitHub Sign Up](https://github.com/signup).  

---

### **3. Enter Your Details**  
- **Username** â†’ Choose a unique username.  
- **Email Address** â†’ Enter a valid email address.  
- **Password** â†’ Choose a strong password.  

---

### **4. Click "Create Account"**  
After filling in the details, click **"Create account"**.  

---

### **5. Solve CAPTCHA**  
GitHub may ask you to complete a **CAPTCHA** to verify you're human.  

---

### **6. Verify Your Email**  
- GitHub will send a **verification email**.  
- Open your email and **click the verification link**.  

---

### **7. Choose Your Preferences**  
- GitHub will ask about **your experience** and **preferred features**.  
- You can **skip this step** or customize your settings.  

---

### **8. Free or Paid Plan**  
- Select the **free plan** (default) or a **paid plan** if needed.  

---

### **9. Finish & Start Using GitHub**  
- After setup, you'll be redirected to your **GitHub dashboard**.  
- You can now **create repositories, contribute to projects, and explore GitHub!** ðŸŽ‰  

